</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bulvaihammersson>BulvaiHammersson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>a_bearhat01</span><br>  Posts: 230<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(12/2/02 7:43:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=708.topic&index=71>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: reply</span><hr size=1> An awful lot of what Xelera referred to above deals with torts. An awful lot of what is wrong with this country deals with torts. Our tort system is nothing short of caustically insane. It's poisonously unhealthy. <br>
<br>
Working in the insurance industry, I deal with lawyers on a daily basis. They aren't really all scum like people make out, but they do survive and prosper in what can only be seen as an inherently flawed and dishonest system.<br>
<br>
We desperately need tort reform.<br>
<br>
More than vote reform, campaign finance reform, tax code reform, or any other reform that doesn't threaten to actively kill us dead if we don't reform it, we need tort reform.<br>
<br>
And we'll NEVER get it.<br>
<br>
Why? Look at the backgrounds of our lawmakers. See how many of them are lawyers? It's a stultifying percentage. Look at the backgrounds of most of the effective lobbyists. An ugly nuber of them are lawyers too. Look at what associations and organisations our lawmakers and lobbyists are part of, who they're money comes from, who their friends are. Our legislative branch is so damned beholden to the lawyers in this country that we might as well say that the lawyers do run the nation.<br>
<br>
And where do lawyers make their money? The real money? The big bucks? <br>
<br>
From torts.<br>
<br>
When that lawyer gets his client awarded a $30000 settlement for stubbing his toe in a car accident, the lawyer walks away with ~$10k of it on average. When that judge loses his mind and awards some utter tard $15mil because she spilled coffee in her own lap, that lawyer gets his third of it.<br>
<br>
So, who wants to lay odds that we'll ever see tort reform when our lawmakers made their money from torts, when their friends make their money from torts, and when the lobbyists for the various Bar assoc etc are paid by people who make their money off torts.<br>
<br>
Tort reform is what we need, and tort reform we'll never get. <p>a_Bearhat01<br>
and<br>
Bulvai Hammersson<br>
